{
  "stem": "8784.5",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 122,
      "text": "You think-- you wonder today how people can come into this country so easy, and in those days, we could not come into this country until 1949.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 123,
      "text": "The four-- the four years in Germany I utilized to continue my education.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 124,
      "text": "A German professor was willing to sit down with me and bring me up through high school education.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 125,
      "text": "I found a man that was-- I started working for as a radio mechanic.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 126,
      "text": "But until 1949, it was all a dream that one day we will be able to leave Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 127,
      "text": "We certainly did not-- the last country in the world we wanted to stay in was Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 128,
      "text": "And it was not until 1949, and the affidavit that my uncle has prepared had no impact on it, it was Truman who permitted 200,000 displaced persons to come into the United States.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 129,
      "text": "And I came under that quota to the United States in 1949.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 130,
      "text": "In March of 1949, the ship that brought us here, the boat that brought us here, the name was USS Jumper.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 131,
      "text": "And in March-- March 13, I arrived in this country.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 132,
      "text": "As you remember March 13, three years ago-- not three years ago, six years ago, was the liquidation of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 133,
      "text": "So March 13 was once again a very important date in my life when I arrived in this country.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 134,
      "text": "I arrived in this country, and my uncle and aunt that lived at that time Passaic, New Jersey, was willing to have me in their home.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 135,
      "text": "And I began searching for work.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 136,
      "text": "Again, I began searching for work at that time as a radio mechanic, but it was not easy to get jobs.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 137,
      "text": "At that time, the GIs were returning from war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 138,
      "text": "Jobs were hard to come by.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
